<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — looking before naming</h2>
  <p class="sub">Whole-class activity. No choice board today — we work this together so everyone's first list of factors is shared evidence we can build on in Block 2.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can list at least 5 factors that might affect whether a planet supports life.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice placeholder">
      <span class="placeholder-tag">Placeholder</span>
      <div class="choice-letter">1</div>
      <div class="choice-title">What can you see?</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">TBD: project the four round, unlabelled planets — Earth, Mars, Venus, TRAPPIST-1e. Students name what they observe (color, size apparent, surface features) before any inference. Observation only.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">2</div>
      <div class="choice-title">What can you guess?</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Same four planets, now with the question: which of these could support life, and how would you decide? Whole-class discussion. Capture every reason offered on the board — no judging right or wrong yet.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">3</div>
      <div class="choice-title">What would you need to know?</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Final move: what data is missing? What would you need to measure or look up before answering with confidence? This gap list becomes the unit's question bank — we'll return to it in Block 10.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

